{
  "global": "Determine the ratio of vertical to horizontal spread of the Moon's scattered reflection in rippled ocean water using ray geometry at grazing incidence (3°).",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "subtask": "Establish the ray geometry for light from the Moon reflecting off rippled water surface.",
      "atomics": [
        "Define the Moon's elevation angle θ = 3° above the horizon.",
        "Express incident ray direction from the Moon traveling downward at angle θ below horizontal: **d_i** = (cos(θ), -sin(θ)).",
        "Model ripple slopes as tilting the surface normal by angle α ≈ σ (maximum ripple slope)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Calculate how ripple slopes deflect reflected rays in the vertical plane.",
      "atomics": [
        "Apply the law of reflection: surface slope α tilts the normal and changes reflected ray angle by approximately 2α.",
        "For ripples with maximum slopes ±σ in the vertical (N-S) plane, reflected rays range from angle (θ - 2σ) to (θ + 2σ).",
        "Decompose the range of reflected ray directions into vertical (z) and horizontal (x) components for small θ and σ."
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Calculate the vertical extent of the scattered reflection.",
      "atomics": [
        "For rays at angles (θ ± 2σ), compute z-component range: from -sin(θ - 2σ) to -sin(θ + 2σ).",
        "Use trigonometric identity: sin(θ + 2σ) - sin(θ - 2σ) = 2cos(θ)sin(2σ) ≈ 4σcos(θ) ≈ 4σ for small θ.",
        "Vertical extent ≈ 4σ (proportional to the z-component range)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Calculate the horizontal extent of the scattered reflection.",
      "atomics": [
        "For rays at angles (θ ± 2σ), compute x-component range: from cos(θ - 2σ) to cos(θ + 2σ).",
        "Use trigonometric identity: cos(θ - 2σ) - cos(θ + 2σ) = 2sin(θ)sin(2σ) ≈ 4σsin(θ) ≈ 4σθ for small θ.",
        "Horizontal extent ≈ 4σθ (proportional to the x-component range, reduced by factor θ due to grazing incidence)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Compute the ratio and apply numerical value.",
      "atomics": [
        "Form the ratio r = (vertical extent) / (horizontal extent) = 4σ / (4σθ) = 1/θ.",
        "Convert θ = 3° to radians: θ = 3 × (π/180) = π/60 ≈ 0.05236 rad.",
        "Calculate r = 1/θ = 60/π ≈ 19.099.",
        "Round to the nearest whole number: r = 19."
      ]
    }
  ],
  "global_atomics": [
    "Verify that the horizontal extent is suppressed by the grazing angle θ because ray deflections perpendicular to the main plane project weakly onto the horizontal direction when θ is small.",
    "Confirm that the ratio 1/θ is independent of ripple slope σ, depending only on the geometry of grazing incidence."
  ],
  "gold_actions": {
    "global": "Calculate the anisotropy of the Moon's scattered reflection caused by grazing incidence (small θ) on rippled water.",
    "subtasks": [
      {
        "subtask": "Set up the ray geometry with Moon at 3° elevation and ripple slopes deflecting rays by ±2σ.",
        "atomics": [
          "Incident rays travel at angle θ = 3° below horizontal: **d_i** = (cos(3°), -sin(3°)).",
          "Ripple slopes ±σ change the surface normal, deflecting reflected rays by ±2σ.",
          "Reflected rays range from (θ - 2σ) to (θ + 2σ) ≈ (3° - 2σ) to (3° + 2σ)."
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Decompose reflected ray spread into vertical and horizontal components using small-angle approximation.",
        "atomics": [
          "z-component (vertical): -sin(θ ± 2σ) ranges over Δz ≈ 4σcos(θ) ≈ 4σ.",
          "x-component (horizontal): cos(θ ± 2σ) ranges over Δx ≈ 4σsin(θ) ≈ 4σ × 0.05236 ≈ 0.209σ.",
          "Angular projection shows horizontal extent is attenuated by factor sin(θ) = θ (in radians)."
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Compute the ratio and numerical result.",
        "atomics": [
          "r = Δz / Δx = 4σ / (4σθ) = 1/θ.",
          "θ = 3° = π/60 rad ≈ 0.05236 rad.",
          "r = 60/π ≈ 19.099.",
          "Round to nearest integer: r = 19."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "global_atomics": [
      "The grazing incidence geometry at small θ produces an anisotropic scatter pattern where vertical spreading dominates horizontal spreading by a factor of 1/θ ≈ 19 for θ = 3°.",
      "The ratio is independent of ripple slope magnitude and depends only on the angle of incidence."
    ]
  }
}
```

FINAL ANSWER: 19
